@startuml
!theme cerulean
title UC-04 - Activity Diagram: Manage Table & Field Mappings

start

:1. Maker (BA/DE) accesses Table & Field Mapping Module;

:2. System displays list of existing Table Mappings;

if (Action?) then (Create Table Mapping)
  :3. Select Integration Profile;
  :4. Enter Source Table & Target File Name Pattern;
  :5. System validates uniqueness;

elseif (Action?) then (Edit Table Mapping)
  :3. Select existing Table Mapping;
  :4. Modify information;

elseif (Action?) then (Deactivate)
  :3. Select Table Mapping;
  :4. System performs Dependency Check;
  if (Has Active Fields?) then (Yes)
    :Show error + list of dependent fields;
    detach
  else (No)
    :5. Set status = Inactive;
  endif

endif

:6. Enter / Manage Field Mappings (Target-Driven);
:7. For each field: Define source_field, target_field, data_type, required, default_value, XREF, date_format...;
:8. System performs validation (duplicate target, required fields...);

:9. Save changes with Pending status + Audit Log;

if (Production?) then (Yes)
  :10. Send for Checker Approval;
  if (Approved?) then (Yes)
    :11. Activate changes;
    :12. Trigger Meta-Schema Cache Refresh;
  else (No)
    :Reject & notify Maker;
    detach
  endif
else
  :11. Activate immediately;
  :12. Trigger Cache Refresh;
endif

stop

@enduml